						               													<description>Self-titled as the &amp;quot;brilliant but vicious&amp;quot; new game. Each player races to move two pawns to their spaces at the end of the board. The board includes several special spaces which can help or hinder your progress. Getting jumped by your opponent moves your pieces back a space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To make things more interesting, each pawn has a special movement. A Starka can move one space diagonally but can jump in any direction. A Schnook can move one space forward, left or right.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board includes the following special squares:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BLACK moves opponent's farthest ahead piece back to any unoccupied square in row his hindmost piece is on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GREEN is a free move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;YELLOW lets you place your piece on any other connecting yellow square in the same block.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RED makes you lose a turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BLUE can be jumped as if it were another piece.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
